isisD13MIB.name: isisD13MIB
isisD13MIB.organization: IETF IS-IS for IP Internets Working Group
isisD13MIB.contactinfo: Jeff Parker Axiowave Networks 200 Nickerson Rd. Marlborough, MA 01752 jparker@axiowave.com
isisD13MIB.description: This document describes a management information base for the IS-IS Routing protocol, as described in ISO 10589, when it is used to construct routing tables for IP networks, as described in RFC 1195. This document defines an experimental portion of the Management Information Base (MIB) for use with network management protocols in the Internet community. This document is based on a 1994 IETF draft by Chris Gunner. This version has been modified to include MIB-II syntax, to exclude portions of the protocol that are not relevant to IP, and to add management support for current practice.

isisD13System.name: isisD13System
isisD13System.description: The object describes system wide attributes.

isisD13SysLevel.name: isisD13SysLevel
isisD13SysLevel.description: This object describes attributes associated with the domain or with the area.

isisD13Circ.name: isisD13Circ
isisD13Circ.description: This object describes attributes associated with one Circuit

isisD13CircLevelValues.name: isisD13CircLevelValues
isisD13CircLevelValues.description: This object describes attributes associated with area or domain relevant within a Circuit.

isisD13Counters.name: isisD13Counters
isisD13Counters.description: This object collects system and circuit counters

isisD13ISAdj.name: isisD13ISAdj
isisD13ISAdj.description: This object describes attributes associated with an adjacent Protocol Peer.

isisD13ReachAddr.name: isisD13ReachAddr
isisD13ReachAddr.description: This object describes attributes associated with a configured address

isisD13IPReachAddr.name: isisD13IPReachAddr
isisD13IPReachAddr.description: This object describes attributes associated with IP routes learned by configuration or through another protocol.

isisD13LSPDataBase.name: isisD13LSPDataBase
isisD13LSPDataBase.description: This object describes the collection of Link State PDUs known to the system.

OSINSAddress.name: OSINSAddress
OSINSAddress.description: OSI Network Service Address, e.g. NSAP, SNPA, or Network Entity Title

AdminState.name: AdminState
AdminState.description: Type used in enabling and disabling a row. Values match those in RFC 2863.

LSPBuffSize.name: LSPBuffSize
LSPBuffSize.description: Integer sub range for LSP size.

SupportedProtocol.name: SupportedProtocol
SupportedProtocol.description: Types of network protocol supported by Integrated IS-IS. The values for ISO8473 and IP are those registered for these protocols in ISO TR9577.

DefaultMetric.name: DefaultMetric
DefaultMetric.description: Integer sub-range for default metric for single hop. ISO 10589 provides for 4 types of metric. Only the 'default' metric is used in practice.

WideMetric.name: WideMetric
WideMetric.description: Wide Metric for IS Neighbors. ISO 10589 provides a 6 bit metric. Traffic Engineering extensions provide 24 bit metrics.

FullMetric.name: FullMetric
FullMetric.description: Full Metric for IP Routes. Traffic Engineering extensions provide 32 bit metrics.

MetricType.name: MetricType
MetricType.description: Is this an Internal or External Metric?

MetricStyle.name: MetricStyle
MetricStyle.description: Do we use 1195 style Metrics or wide metrics.

IsisPDUHeader.name: IsisPDUHeader
IsisPDUHeader.description: A block to contain the header from a PDU.

Unsigned16TC.name: Unsigned16TC
Unsigned16TC.description: An Unsigned32 further restricted to 16 Bits. Note that the ASN.1 BER encoding may still require 24 Bits for some values.

Unsigned8TC.name: Unsigned8TC
Unsigned8TC.description: An Unsigned32 further restricted to 8 Bits. Note that the ASN.1 BER encoding may still require 16 Bits for some values.

isisD13SysTable.name: isisD13SysTable
isisD13SysTable.description: The set of instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system.

isisD13SysEntry.name: isisD13SysEntry
isisD13SysEntry.description: Each row defines information specific to a single instance of the IS-IS protocol existing on the system.

isisD13SysInstance.name: isisD13SysInstance
isisD13SysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behavior.

isisD13SysVersion.name: isisD13SysVersion
isisD13SysVersion.description: The version number of the IS-IS protocol which this instance implements.

isisD13SysType.name: isisD13SysType
isisD13SysType.description: The type of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

isisD13SysID.name: isisD13SysID
isisD13SysID.description: The ID for this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This value is appended to each of the area addresses to form the Network Entity Titles. The derivation of a value for this object is implementation-specific. Some implementations may automatically assign values and not permit an SNMP write, while others may require the value to be set manually.

isisD13SysMaxPathSplits.name: isisD13SysMaxPathSplits
isisD13SysMaxPathSplits.description: Maximum number of paths with equal routing metric value which it is permitted to split between. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

isisD13SysMaxLSPGenInt.name: isisD13SysMaxLSPGenInt
isisD13SysMaxLSPGenInt.description: Maximum interval, in seconds, between generated LSPs by this instance of the protocol. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior. Should be at least 300 seconds less than isisD13SysMaxAge.

isisD13SysPollESHelloRate.name: isisD13SysPollESHelloRate
isisD13SysPollESHelloRate.description: The value, in seconds, to be used for the suggested ES configuration timer in ISH PDUs when soliciting the ES configuration.

isisD13SysWaitTime.name: isisD13SysWaitTime
isisD13SysWaitTime.description: Number of seconds to delay in waiting state before entering on state. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior.

isisD13SysAdminState.name: isisD13SysAdminState
isisD13SysAdminState.description: The administrative state of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. Setting this object to the value 'on' when its current value is 'off' enables operation of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol.

isisD13SysLogAdjacencyChanges.name: isisD13SysLogAdjacencyChanges
isisD13SysLogAdjacencyChanges.description: If true, causes IS-IS to generate a log message when an IS-IS adjacency changes state (up or down).

isisD13SysNextCircIndex.name: isisD13SysNextCircIndex
isisD13SysNextCircIndex.description: This object is used to assign values to isisD13CircIndex as described in 'Textual Conventions for SNMPv2'. The network manager reads this object, and then writes the value back as the isisD13CircIndex in a SET that creates a new instance of isisD13CircEntry. If the SET fails with the code 'inconsistentValue', then the process must be repeated; If the SET succeeds, then the object is incremented, and the new isisD13Circuit is created according to the manager's directions.

isisD13SysL2toL1Leaking.name: isisD13SysL2toL1Leaking
isisD13SysL2toL1Leaking.description: If true, allow the router to leak L2 routes into L1.

isisD13SysMaxAge.name: isisD13SysMaxAge
isisD13SysMaxAge.description: Value to place in RemainingLifeTime field of the LSPs we generate. This is should be at least 300 seconds greater than isisD13SysMaxLSPGenInt.

isisD13SysReceiveLSPBufferSize.name: isisD13SysReceiveLSPBufferSize
isisD13SysReceiveLSPBufferSize.description: Size of the largest Buffer we are designed or configured to store. This should be at least as big as the maximum isisD13SysOrigLSPBuffSize supported by the system. If resources allow, we will store and flood LSPs larger than isisD13SysReceiveLSPBufferSize, as this can help avoid problems in networks with different values for isisD13SysOrigLSPBuffSize.

isisD13SysExistState.name: isisD13SysExistState
isisD13SysExistState.description: The state of the IS-IS router. Turning this to state 'destroy' forces the router to forget all the current configuration. Setting the state to 'notInService' stops protocol processing, but retains the configuration.

isisD13ManAreaAddrTable.name: isisD13ManAreaAddrTable
isisD13ManAreaAddrTable.description: The set of manual area addresses configured on this Intermediate System.

isisD13ManAreaAddrEntry.name: isisD13ManAreaAddrEntry
isisD13ManAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one area address manually configured on this system

isisD13ManAreaAddr.name: isisD13ManAreaAddr
isisD13ManAreaAddr.description: A manually configured area address for this system. This object follows the index behavior. Note: an index for the entry {1, {49.0001} active} in this table would be the ordered pair (1, (0x03 0x49 0x00 0x01)), as the length of an Octet string is part of the OID.

isisD13ManAreaAddrExistState.name: isisD13ManAreaAddrExistState
isisD13ManAreaAddrExistState.description: The state of the isisD13ManAreaAddrEntry. This object follows the Row Status behavior. If the isisD13SysAdminState for this instance of the IS-IS protocol is 'on', and an attempt is made to set this object to the value 'destroy' or 'notInService' when this is the only isisD13ManAreaAddrEntry in state 'active' for this instance of the IS-IS protocol should return inconsistentValue.

isisD13AreaAddrTable.name: isisD13AreaAddrTable
isisD13AreaAddrTable.description: The union of the sets of area addresses reported in all Level 1 LSPs with segment number zero received by this instance of the protocol from Intermediate Systems which are reachable via Level 1 routing.

isisD13AreaAddrEntry.name: isisD13AreaAddrEntry
isisD13AreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one area address reported in a Level 1 LSP received by this instance of the IS-IS protocol.

isisD13AreaAddr.name: isisD13AreaAddr
isisD13AreaAddr.description: An area address reported in a Level 1 LSP received by this instance of the IS-IS protocol.

isisD13SysProtSuppTable.name: isisD13SysProtSuppTable
isisD13SysProtSuppTable.description: This table contains the manually configured set of protocols supported by each instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol.

isisD13SysProtSuppEntry.name: isisD13SysProtSuppEntry
isisD13SysProtSuppEntry.description: Each entry contains one protocol supported by an instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol.

isisD13SysProtSuppProtocol.name: isisD13SysProtSuppProtocol
isisD13SysProtSuppProtocol.description: One supported protocol. This object follows the index behavior.

isisD13SysProtSuppExistState.name: isisD13SysProtSuppExistState
isisD13SysProtSuppExistState.description: The state of the isisD13SysProtSuppEntry. This object follows the RowStatus behavior.

isisD13SummAddrTable.name: isisD13SummAddrTable
isisD13SummAddrTable.description: The set of IP summary addresses to use in forming summary TLVs originated by this Intermediate System. An administrator may use a summary address to combine and modify IP Reachability announcements. If the Intermediate system can reach any subset of the summary address, the summary address will be announced instead, at the configured metric.

isisD13SummAddrEntry.name: isisD13SummAddrEntry
isisD13SummAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP summary address.

isisD13SummAddressType.name: isisD13SummAddressType
isisD13SummAddressType.description: The Type of IP address for this summary address. This object follows the index behavior.

isisD13SummAddress.name: isisD13SummAddress
isisD13SummAddress.description: The IP Address value for this summary address. This object follows the index behavior.

isisD13SummAddrPrefixLen.name: isisD13SummAddrPrefixLen
isisD13SummAddrPrefixLen.description: The Length of the IP NetMask for this summary address.

isisD13SummAddrExistState.name: isisD13SummAddrExistState
isisD13SummAddrExistState.description: The existence state of this summary address. This object follows the row status behavior.

isisD13SummAddrMetric.name: isisD13SummAddrMetric
isisD13SummAddrMetric.description: The metric value to announce this summary address with in LSPs generated by this system.

isisD13SummAddrFullMetric.name: isisD13SummAddrFullMetric
isisD13SummAddrFullMetric.description: The wide metric value to announce this summary address with in LSPs generated by this system.

isisD13RedistributeAddrTable.name: isisD13RedistributeAddrTable
isisD13RedistributeAddrTable.description: This table provides criteria to decide if a route should be leaked from L2 to L1 when Domain Wide Prefix leaking is enabled. Addresses that match the summary mask in the table will be announced at L1 by routers when isisD13SysL2toL1Leaking is enabled. Routes that fall into the ranges specified are announced as is, without being summarized. Routes that do not match a summary mask are not announced.

isisD13RedistributeAddrEntry.name: isisD13RedistributeAddrEntry
isisD13RedistributeAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP summary address to manage leaking L2 addresses into L1.

isisD13RedistributeAddrType.name: isisD13RedistributeAddrType
isisD13RedistributeAddrType.description: The Type of IP address for this summary address. This object follows the index behavior.

isisD13RedistributeAddrAddress.name: isisD13RedistributeAddrAddress
isisD13RedistributeAddrAddress.description: The IP Address value for this summary address. This object follows the index behavior.

isisD13RedistributeAddrPrefixLen.name: isisD13RedistributeAddrPrefixLen
isisD13RedistributeAddrPrefixLen.description: The Length of the IP NetMask for this summary address.

isisD13RedistributeAddrExistState.name: isisD13RedistributeAddrExistState
isisD13RedistributeAddrExistState.description: The existence state of this summary address. This object follows the row status behavior.

isisD13RouterTable.name: isisD13RouterTable
isisD13RouterTable.description: The set of hostnames and router ID.

isisD13RouterEntry.name: isisD13RouterEntry
isisD13RouterEntry.description: Each entry tracks information about one peer at one level.

isisD13RouterSysID.name: isisD13RouterSysID
isisD13RouterSysID.description: The System ID of the Router Peer.

isisD13RouterLevel.name: isisD13RouterLevel
isisD13RouterLevel.description: The level of this Intermediate System.

isisD13RouterHostName.name: isisD13RouterHostName
isisD13RouterHostName.description: The hostname listed in LSP, or NULL if none.

isisD13RouterID.name: isisD13RouterID
isisD13RouterID.description: The Router ID of the Peer found in LSP, or NULL if none.

isisD13SysLevelTable.name: isisD13SysLevelTable
isisD13SysLevelTable.description: Level specific information about the System.

isisD13SysLevelEntry.name: isisD13SysLevelEntry
isisD13SysLevelEntry.description: Describe variables defined for Area or Domain.

isisD13SysLevelIndex.name: isisD13SysLevelIndex
isisD13SysLevelIndex.description: The level that this entry describes.

isisD13SysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize.name: isisD13SysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize
isisD13SysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize.description: The maximum size of LSPs and SNPs originated by this instance of the protocol at this level. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

isisD13SysLevelMinLSPGenInt.name: isisD13SysLevelMinLSPGenInt
isisD13SysLevelMinLSPGenInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between successive generation of LSPs with the same LSPID at this level by this instance of the protocol. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior.

isisD13SysLevelOverloadState.name: isisD13SysLevelOverloadState
isisD13SysLevelOverloadState.description: The Overload state of the database at this level. The value 'overloaded' indicates a database that is low on an essential resource, such as memory. The administrator may indirectly force the state to 'waiting' when the router is initializing by setting the object isisD13SysLevelSetOverload. If the state is waiting or overloaded, we originate LSPs with the Overload bit set.

isisD13SysLevelSetOverload.name: isisD13SysLevelSetOverload
isisD13SysLevelSetOverload.description: Administratively set the overload bit for the level. The overload bit will continue to be set if the implementation runs out of memory, independent of this variable

isisD13SysLevelSetOverloadUntil.name: isisD13SysLevelSetOverloadUntil
isisD13SysLevelSetOverloadUntil.description: If set, the overload bit should be set, and cleared after sysUpTime exceeds this value.

isisD13SysLevelMetricStyle.name: isisD13SysLevelMetricStyle
isisD13SysLevelMetricStyle.description: Which style of Metric do we generate in our LSPs at this level? This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

isisD13SysLevelSPFConsiders.name: isisD13SysLevelSPFConsiders
isisD13SysLevelSPFConsiders.description: Which style of Metric do we consider in our SPF computation at this level?

isisD13SysLevelTEEnabled.name: isisD13SysLevelTEEnabled
isisD13SysLevelTEEnabled.description: Do we do Traffic Engineering at this level?

isisD13CircTable.name: isisD13CircTable
isisD13CircTable.description: The table of circuits used by each instance of Integrated IS-IS on this system.

isisD13CircEntry.name: isisD13CircEntry
isisD13CircEntry.description: An isisD13CircEntry exists for each circuit used by Integrated IS-IS on this system.

isisD13CircIndex.name: isisD13CircIndex
isisD13CircIndex.description: The identifier of this circuit, unique within the instance of the IS-IS protocol. This object follows the index behavior. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and need not have any relation to any protocol value.

isisD13CircIfIndex.name: isisD13CircIfIndex
isisD13CircIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex for the interface to which this circuit corresponds. This object cannot be modified after creation

isisD13CircIfSubIndex.name: isisD13CircIfSubIndex
isisD13CircIfSubIndex.description: A specifier for the part of the interface ifIndex to which this circuit corresponds, such as a DLCI or VPI/VCI. This object cannot be modified after creation

isisD13CircAdminState.name: isisD13CircAdminState
isisD13CircAdminState.description: The administrative state of the circuit. This object follows the AdminState behavior.

isisD13CircExistState.name: isisD13CircExistState
isisD13CircExistState.description: The existence state of this circuit. This object follows the Row Status behavior. Setting the state to 'notInService' halts the generation and processing of IS-IS protocol PDUs on this circuit. Setting the state to destroy will also erase any configuration associated with the circuit.

isisD13CircType.name: isisD13CircType
isisD13CircType.description: The type of the circuit. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior. The type specified must be compatible with the type of the interface defined by the value of isisD13CircIfIndex.

isisD13CircExtDomain.name: isisD13CircExtDomain
isisD13CircExtDomain.description: If true, suppress normal transmission of and interpretation of Intra-domain IS-IS PDUs on this circuit.

isisD13CircLevel.name: isisD13CircLevel
isisD13CircLevel.description: Indicates which type of packets will be sent and accepted on this circuit. The values used will be modified by the settings of isisD13SysType. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

isisD13CircPassiveCircuit.name: isisD13CircPassiveCircuit
isisD13CircPassiveCircuit.description: Should we include this interface in LSPs, even if it is not running the IS-IS Protocol?

isisD13CircMeshGroupEnabled.name: isisD13CircMeshGroupEnabled
isisD13CircMeshGroupEnabled.description: Is this port a member of a mesh group, or blocked? Circuits in the same mesh group act as a virtual multiaccess network. LSPs seen on one circuit in a mesh group will not be flooded to another circuit in the same mesh group.

isisD13CircMeshGroup.name: isisD13CircMeshGroup
isisD13CircMeshGroup.description: Circuits in the same mesh group act as a virtual multiaccess network. LSPs seen on one circuit in a mesh group will not be flooded to another circuit in the same mesh group. If isisD13CircMeshGroupEnabled is inactive or blocked, this value is ignored.

isisD13CircSmallHellos.name: isisD13CircSmallHellos
isisD13CircSmallHellos.description: Can we send unpadded hellos on LAN circuits? False means LAN Hellos must be padded. Implementations should allow the administrator to read this value. An implementation need not be able to support unpadded hellos to be conformant.

isisD13CircLastUpTime.name: isisD13CircLastUpTime
isisD13CircLastUpTime.description: If the circuit is enabled, the value of sysUpTime when isisD13CircAdminState most recently entered the state on. If the circuit is not on, the value of sysUpTime when the circuit last entered state on, 0 if the circuit has never been on.

isisD13Circ3WayEnabled.name: isisD13Circ3WayEnabled
isisD13Circ3WayEnabled.description: Is this circuit enabled to run 3Way handshake?

isisD13CircExtendedCircID.name: isisD13CircExtendedCircID
isisD13CircExtendedCircID.description: A unique value to be used as the extended circuit ID in 3Way handshake.

isisD13CircLevelTable.name: isisD13CircLevelTable
isisD13CircLevelTable.description: Level specific information about circuits used by IS-IS

isisD13CircLevelEntry.name: isisD13CircLevelEntry
isisD13CircLevelEntry.description: An isisD13CircLevelEntry exists for each level on each circuit used by Integrated IS-IS on this system.

isisD13CircLevelIndex.name: isisD13CircLevelIndex
isisD13CircLevelIndex.description: The level that this entry describes.

isisD13CircLevelMetric.name: isisD13CircLevelMetric
isisD13CircLevelMetric.description: The metric value of this circuit for this level.

isisD13CircLevelWideMetric.name: isisD13CircLevelWideMetric
isisD13CircLevelWideMetric.description: The wide metric value of this circuit for this level.

isisD13CircLevelISPriority.name: isisD13CircLevelISPriority
isisD13CircLevelISPriority.description: The priority for becoming LAN Designated Intermediate System at this level.

isisD13CircLevelIDOctet.name: isisD13CircLevelIDOctet
isisD13CircLevelIDOctet.description: A one byte identifier that can be used in protocol packets to identify a circuit. Values of isisD13CircLevelIDOctet do not need to be unique. They are only required to differ on LANs where the Intermediate System is the Designated Intermediate System.

isisD13CircLevelID.name: isisD13CircLevelID
isisD13CircLevelID.description: The ID of the circuit allocated during initialization. If no value has been negotiated (either because the adjacency is to an End System, or because initialization has not yet successfully completed), this object has the value which would be proposed for this circuit (i.e. the concatenation of the local system ID and the one byte isisD13CircLevelIDOctet for this circuit.

isisD13CircLevelDesIS.name: isisD13CircLevelDesIS
isisD13CircLevelDesIS.description: The ID of the LAN Designated Intermediate System on this circuit at this level. If, for any reason, this system is not partaking in the relevant Designated Intermediate System election process, then the value returned is the zero length OCTET STRING.

isisD13CircLevelHelloMultiplier.name: isisD13CircLevelHelloMultiplier
isisD13CircLevelHelloMultiplier.description: This value is multiplied by the corresponding HelloTimer and the result in seconds (rounded up) is used as the holding time in transmitted hellos, to be used by receivers of hello packets from this IS

isisD13CircLevelHelloTimer.name: isisD13CircLevelHelloTimer
isisD13CircLevelHelloTimer.description: Maximum period, in milliseconds, between IIH PDUs on multiaccess networks at this level for LANs. The value at level 1 is used as the period between Hellos on L1L2 point to point circuits. Setting this value at level 2 on an L1L2 point to point circuit will result in an error of InconsistentValue. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior.

isisD13CircLevelDRHelloTimer.name: isisD13CircLevelDRHelloTimer
isisD13CircLevelDRHelloTimer.description: Period, in milliseconds, between Hello PDUs on multiaccess networks when this IS is the Designated Intermediate System. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior.

isisD13CircLevelLSPThrottle.name: isisD13CircLevelLSPThrottle
isisD13CircLevelLSPThrottle.description: Minimal interval of time, in milliseconds, between transmissions of LSPs on an interface at this level.

isisD13CircLevelMinLSPRetransInt.name: isisD13CircLevelMinLSPRetransInt
isisD13CircLevelMinLSPRetransInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between re-transmission of an LSP at this level. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior. Note that isisD13CircLevelLSPThrottle controls how fast we send back to back LSPs. This variable controls how fast we re-send the same LSP.

isisD13CircLevelCSNPInterval.name: isisD13CircLevelCSNPInterval
isisD13CircLevelCSNPInterval.description: Interval of time, in seconds, between periodic transmission of a complete set of CSNPs on multiaccess networks if this router is the designated router at this level.

isisD13CircLevelPartSNPInterval.name: isisD13CircLevelPartSNPInterval
isisD13CircLevelPartSNPInterval.description: Minimum interval in seconds between sending Partial Sequence Number PDUs at this level. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior.

isisD13SystemCounterTable.name: isisD13SystemCounterTable
isisD13SystemCounterTable.description: System wide counters for one instance of the IS-IS protocol on the system.

isisD13SysStatLevel.name: isisD13SysStatLevel
isisD13SysStatLevel.description: The level that this entry describes.

isisD13SysStatCorrLSPs.name: isisD13SysStatCorrLSPs
isisD13SysStatCorrLSPs.description: Number of corrupted in-memory LSPs detected. LSPs received from the wire with a bad checksum are silently dropped and not counted.

isisD13SysStatAuthTypeFails.name: isisD13SysStatAuthTypeFails
isisD13SysStatAuthTypeFails.description: The number of authentication type mismatches recognized by this instance of the protocol.

isisD13SysStatAuthFails.name: isisD13SysStatAuthFails
isisD13SysStatAuthFails.description: The number of authentication failures recognized by this instance of the protocol.

isisD13SysStatLSPDbaseOloads.name: isisD13SysStatLSPDbaseOloads
isisD13SysStatLSPDbaseOloads.description: Number of times the LSP database has become overloaded.

isisD13SysStatManAddrDropFromAreas.name: isisD13SysStatManAddrDropFromAreas
isisD13SysStatManAddrDropFromAreas.description: Number of times a manual address has been dropped from the area.

isisD13SysStatAttmptToExMaxSeqNums.name: isisD13SysStatAttmptToExMaxSeqNums
isisD13SysStatAttmptToExMaxSeqNums.description: Number of times the IS has attempted to exceed the maximum sequence number.

isisD13SysStatSeqNumSkips.name: isisD13SysStatSeqNumSkips
isisD13SysStatSeqNumSkips.description: Number of times a sequence number skip has occurred.

isisD13SysStatOwnLSPPurges.name: isisD13SysStatOwnLSPPurges
isisD13SysStatOwnLSPPurges.description: Number of times a zero-aged copy of the system's own LSP is received from some other node.

isisD13SysStatIDFieldLenMismatches.name: isisD13SysStatIDFieldLenMismatches
isisD13SysStatIDFieldLenMismatches.description: Number of times a PDU is received with a different value for ID field length to that of the receiving system.

isisD13SysStatMaxAreaAddrMismatches.name: isisD13SysStatMaxAreaAddrMismatches
isisD13SysStatMaxAreaAddrMismatches.description: Number of times a PDU is received with a different value for MaximumAreaAddresses from that of the receiving system.

isisD13SysStatSPFRuns.name: isisD13SysStatSPFRuns
isisD13SysStatSPFRuns.description: Number of times we ran SPF at this level.

isisD13CircuitCounterTable.name: isisD13CircuitCounterTable
isisD13CircuitCounterTable.description: Circuit specific counters for one instance of the IS-IS protocol on the system.

isisD13CircuitCounterEntry.name: isisD13CircuitCounterEntry
isisD13CircuitCounterEntry.description: An isisD13CircCountEntry exists for each circuit used by Integrated IS-IS on this system.

isisD13CircuitType.name: isisD13CircuitType
isisD13CircuitType.description: What type of circuit saw these counts? The point to point Hello PDU includes both L1 and L2, and ISs form a single adjacency on point to point links. Thus we combine counts on point to point links into one group.

isisD13CircAdjChanges.name: isisD13CircAdjChanges
isisD13CircAdjChanges.description: The number of times an adjacency state change has occurred on this circuit.

isisD13CircNumAdj.name: isisD13CircNumAdj
isisD13CircNumAdj.description: The number of adjacencies on this circuit.

isisD13CircInitFails.name: isisD13CircInitFails
isisD13CircInitFails.description: The number of times initialization of this circuit has failed.

isisD13CircRejAdjs.name: isisD13CircRejAdjs
isisD13CircRejAdjs.description: The number of times an adjacency has been rejected on this circuit.

isisD13CircIDFieldLenMismatches.name: isisD13CircIDFieldLenMismatches
isisD13CircIDFieldLenMismatches.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with an ID field length different to that for this system has been received.

isisD13CircMaxAreaAddrMismatches.name: isisD13CircMaxAreaAddrMismatches
isisD13CircMaxAreaAddrMismatches.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with a max area address field different to that for this system has been received.

isisD13CircAuthTypeFails.name: isisD13CircAuthTypeFails
isisD13CircAuthTypeFails.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with an auth type field different to that for this system has been received.

isisD13CircAuthFails.name: isisD13CircAuthFails
isisD13CircAuthFails.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with the correct auth type has failed to pass authentication validation.

isisD13CircLANDesISChanges.name: isisD13CircLANDesISChanges
isisD13CircLANDesISChanges.description: The number of times the Designated IS has changed on this circuit at this level. If the circuit is point to point, this count is zero.

isisD13PacketCounterTable.name: isisD13PacketCounterTable
isisD13PacketCounterTable.description: Information about IS-IS protocol traffic at one level on one circuit in one direction

isisD13PacketCounterEntry.name: isisD13PacketCounterEntry
isisD13PacketCounterEntry.description: Information about IS-IS protocol traffic at one level on one circuit in one direction

isisD13PacketCountLevel.name: isisD13PacketCountLevel
isisD13PacketCountLevel.description: The level at which these PDU counts have been collected.

isisD13PacketCountDirection.name: isisD13PacketCountDirection
isisD13PacketCountDirection.description: Were we sending or receiving these PDUs?

isisD13PacketCountIIHello.name: isisD13PacketCountIIHello
isisD13PacketCountIIHello.description: The number of IS-IS Hello PDUs seen in this direction at this level. Point-to-Point IIH PDUs are counted at Level 1 if the value of their Circuit Type field is 1, and are counted at Level 2 otherwise.

isisD13PacketCountISHello.name: isisD13PacketCountISHello
isisD13PacketCountISHello.description: The number of ES-IS Hello PDUs seen in this direction. ISH PDUs are counted at the lowest enabled level: at L1 on L1 or L1L2 circuits, and at L2 otherwise.

isisD13PacketCountESHello.name: isisD13PacketCountESHello
isisD13PacketCountESHello.description: The number of ES Hello PDUs seen in this direction. ESH PDUs are counted at the lowest enabled level: at L1 on L1 or L1L2 circuits, and at L2 otherwise.

isisD13PacketCountLSP.name: isisD13PacketCountLSP
isisD13PacketCountLSP.description: The number of IS-IS LSPs seen in this direction at this level.

isisD13PacketCountCSNP.name: isisD13PacketCountCSNP
isisD13PacketCountCSNP.description: The number of IS-IS CSNPs seen in this direction at this level.

isisD13PacketCountPSNP.name: isisD13PacketCountPSNP
isisD13PacketCountPSNP.description: The number of IS-IS PSNPs seen in this direction at this level.

isisD13PacketCountUnknown.name: isisD13PacketCountUnknown
isisD13PacketCountUnknown.description: The number of unknown IS-IS PDUs seen at this level.

isisD13ISAdjTable.name: isisD13ISAdjTable
isisD13ISAdjTable.description: The table of adjacencies to Intermediate Systems.

isisD13ISAdjEntry.name: isisD13ISAdjEntry
isisD13ISAdjEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one adjacency to an Intermediate System on this system.

isisD13ISAdjIndex.name: isisD13ISAdjIndex
isisD13ISAdjIndex.description: A unique value identifying the IS adjacency from all other such adjacencies on this circuit. This value is assigned by the system when the adjacency is created automatically.

isisD13ISAdj3WayState.name: isisD13ISAdj3WayState
isisD13ISAdj3WayState.description: The 3Way state of the adjacency. These are picked to match the historical on-the-wire representation of the 3Way state, and are not intended to match isisD13ISAdjState.

isisD13ISAdjNeighSNPAAddress.name: isisD13ISAdjNeighSNPAAddress
isisD13ISAdjNeighSNPAAddress.description: The SNPA address of the neighboring system.

isisD13ISAdjNeighSysType.name: isisD13ISAdjNeighSysType
isisD13ISAdjNeighSysType.description: The type of the neighboring system.

isisD13ISAdjNeighSysID.name: isisD13ISAdjNeighSysID
isisD13ISAdjNeighSysID.description: The system ID of the neighboring Intermediate System.

isisD13ISAdjNbrExtendedCircID.name: isisD13ISAdjNbrExtendedCircID
isisD13ISAdjNbrExtendedCircID.description: The 4 byte Extended Circuit ID learned from the Neighbor during 3-way handshake, or 0.

isisD13ISAdjUsage.name: isisD13ISAdjUsage
isisD13ISAdjUsage.description: How is the adjacency used? On a point-to-point link, this might be level1and2, but on a LAN, the usage will be level1 on the adjacency between peers at level 1, and level2 for the adjacency between peers at level 2.

isisD13ISAdjHoldTimer.name: isisD13ISAdjHoldTimer
isisD13ISAdjHoldTimer.description: The holding time in seconds for this adjacency. This value is based on received IIH PDUs and the elapsed time since receipt.

isisD13ISAdjNeighPriority.name: isisD13ISAdjNeighPriority
isisD13ISAdjNeighPriority.description: Priority of the neighboring Intermediate System for becoming the Designated Intermediate System.

isisD13ISAdjLastUpTime.name: isisD13ISAdjLastUpTime
isisD13ISAdjLastUpTime.description: If the isisD13ISAdjState is in state 'up', the value of sysUpTime when the adjacency most recently entered the state 'up', or 0 if it has never been in state 'up'.

isisD13ISAdjAreaAddrTable.name: isisD13ISAdjAreaAddrTable
isisD13ISAdjAreaAddrTable.description: This table contains the set of Area Addresses of neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

isisD13ISAdjAreaAddrEntry.name: isisD13ISAdjAreaAddrEntry
isisD13ISAdjAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one Area Address reported by a neighboring Intermediate System in its IIH PDUs.

isisD13ISAdjAreaAddrIndex.name: isisD13ISAdjAreaAddrIndex
isisD13ISAdjAreaAddrIndex.description: An index for the areas associated with one neighbor. This provides a simpler way to walk the table.

isisD13ISAdjAreaAddress.name: isisD13ISAdjAreaAddress
isisD13ISAdjAreaAddress.description: One Area Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

isisD13ISAdjIPAddrTable.name: isisD13ISAdjIPAddrTable
isisD13ISAdjIPAddrTable.description: This table contains the set of IP Addresses of neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

isisD13ISAdjIPAddrEntry.name: isisD13ISAdjIPAddrEntry
isisD13ISAdjIPAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP Address reported by a neighboring Intermediate System in its IIH PDUs.

isisD13ISAdjIPAddrIndex.name: isisD13ISAdjIPAddrIndex
isisD13ISAdjIPAddrIndex.description: An index to this table which identifies the IP addresss to which this entry belongs.

isisD13ISAdjIPAddressType.name: isisD13ISAdjIPAddressType
isisD13ISAdjIPAddressType.description: The type of one IP Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

isisD13ISAdjIPAddress.name: isisD13ISAdjIPAddress
isisD13ISAdjIPAddress.description: One IP Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

isisD13ISAdjProtSuppTable.name: isisD13ISAdjProtSuppTable
isisD13ISAdjProtSuppTable.description: This table contains the set of protocols supported by neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

isisD13ISAdjProtSuppEntry.name: isisD13ISAdjProtSuppEntry
isisD13ISAdjProtSuppEntry.description: Each entry contains one protocol supported by a neighboring Intermediate System as reported in its IIH PDUs.

isisD13ISAdjProtSuppProtocol.name: isisD13ISAdjProtSuppProtocol
isisD13ISAdjProtSuppProtocol.description: One supported protocol as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

isisD13RATable.name: isisD13RATable
isisD13RATable.description: The table of Reachable Addresses to NSAPs or Address Prefixes.

isisD13RAEntry.name: isisD13RAEntry
isisD13RAEntry.description: Each entry defines a Reachable Address to a NSAP or Address Prefix.

isisD13RAIndex.name: isisD13RAIndex
isisD13RAIndex.description: The identifier for this isisD13RAEntry. This value must be unique amongst all Reachable Addresses on the same parent Circuit. This object follows the index and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

isisD13RAExistState.name: isisD13RAExistState
isisD13RAExistState.description: The existence state of this Reachable Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

isisD13RAAdminState.name: isisD13RAAdminState
isisD13RAAdminState.description: The administrative state of the Reachable Address. This object follows the AdminState and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

isisD13RAAddrPrefix.name: isisD13RAAddrPrefix
isisD13RAAddrPrefix.description: The destination of this Reachable Address. This is an Address Prefix. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

isisD13RAMapType.name: isisD13RAMapType
isisD13RAMapType.description: The type of mapping to be employed to ascertain the SNPA Address which should be used in forwarding PDUs for this Reachable Address prefix. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior. The following values of mapping type are defined: none: The mapping is null because the neighbor SNPA is implicit by nature of the subnetwork (e.g. a point-to-point linkage). explicit: The subnetwork addresses in the object isisD13RASNPAAddress is to be used. extractIDI: The SNPA is embedded in the IDI of the destination NSAP Address. The mapping algorithm extracts the SNPA to be used according to the format and encoding rules of ISO8473/Add2. This SNPA extraction algorithm can be used in conjunction with Reachable Address prefixes from the X.121, F.69, E.163 and E.164 addressing subdomains. extractDSP: All, or a suffix, of the SNPA is embedded in the DSP of the destination address. This SNPA extraction algorithm extracts the embedded subnetwork addressing information by performing a logical AND of the isisD13RASNPAMask object value with the destination address. The part of the SNPA extracted from the destination NSAP is appended to the isisD13RASNPAPrefix object value to form the next hop subnetwork addressing information.

isisD13RAMetric.name: isisD13RAMetric
isisD13RAMetric.description: The metric value for reaching the specified prefix over this circuit. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13RAMetricType.name: isisD13RAMetricType
isisD13RAMetricType.description: Indicates whether the metric is internal or external. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13RASNPAAddress.name: isisD13RASNPAAddress
isisD13RASNPAAddress.description: The SNPA Address to which a PDU may be forwarded in order to reach a destination which matches the address prefix of the Reachable Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13RASNPAMask.name: isisD13RASNPAMask
isisD13RASNPAMask.description: A bit mask with 1 bits indicating the positions in the effective destination address from which embedded SNPA information is to be extracted. For the extraction the first octet of the isisD13RASNPAMask object value is aligned with the first octet (AFI) of the NSAP Address. If the isisD13RASNPAMask object value and NSAP Address are of different lengths, the shorter of the two is logically padded with zeros before performing the extraction. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13RASNPAPrefix.name: isisD13RASNPAPrefix
isisD13RASNPAPrefix.description: A fixed SNPA prefix for use when the isisD13RAMapType is extractDSP. The SNPA Address to use is formed by concatenating the fixed SNPA prefix with a variable SNPA part that is extracted from the effective destination address. For Reachable Address prefixes in which the entire SNPA is embedded in the DSP the SNPA Prefix shall be null. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13RAType.name: isisD13RAType
isisD13RAType.description: The type of Reachable address. Those of type manual are created by the network manager. Those of type automatic are created through propagation of routing information from another routing protocol (eg. IDRP).

isisD13IPRATable.name: isisD13IPRATable
isisD13IPRATable.description: The table of IP Reachable Addresses to networks, subnetworks or hosts either manually configured or learned from another protocol.

isisD13IPRAEntry.name: isisD13IPRAEntry
isisD13IPRAEntry.description: Each entry defines an IP Reachable Address to a network, subnetwork or host.

isisD13IPRADestType.name: isisD13IPRADestType
isisD13IPRADestType.description: The type of this IP Reachable Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13IPRADest.name: isisD13IPRADest
isisD13IPRADest.description: The destination of this IP Reachable Address. This is either a network address, subnetwork address or host address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13IPRADestPrefixLen.name: isisD13IPRADestPrefixLen
isisD13IPRADestPrefixLen.description: The length of the IP Netmask for Reachability Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13IPRANextHopType.name: isisD13IPRANextHopType
isisD13IPRANextHopType.description: The type of the IP next hop address.

isisD13IPRANextHop.name: isisD13IPRANextHop
isisD13IPRANextHop.description: The IP next hop to this destination.

isisD13IPRAType.name: isisD13IPRAType
isisD13IPRAType.description: The type of this IP Reachable Address. Those of type manual are created by the network manager. Those of type automatic are created through propagation of routing information from another routing protocol. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13IPRAExistState.name: isisD13IPRAExistState
isisD13IPRAExistState.description: The state of this IP Reachable Address. This object follows the ExistenceState and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

isisD13IPRAAdminState.name: isisD13IPRAAdminState
isisD13IPRAAdminState.description: The administrative state of the IP Reachable Address. This object follows the AdminState and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

isisD13IPRAMetric.name: isisD13IPRAMetric
isisD13IPRAMetric.description: The metric value for reaching the specified destination over this circuit. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13IPRAMetricType.name: isisD13IPRAMetricType
isisD13IPRAMetricType.description: Indicates whether the metric is internal or external. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13IPRAFullMetric.name: isisD13IPRAFullMetric
isisD13IPRAFullMetric.description: The wide metric value for reaching the specified destination over this circuit. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13IPRASNPAAddress.name: isisD13IPRASNPAAddress
isisD13IPRASNPAAddress.description: The SNPA Address to which a PDU may be forwarded in order to reach a destination which matches this IP Reachable Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

isisD13LSPSummaryEntry.name: isisD13LSPSummaryEntry
isisD13LSPSummaryEntry.description: Each entry describes an LSP current stored in the system.

isisD13LSPLevel.name: isisD13LSPLevel
isisD13LSPLevel.description: At which level does this LSP appear?

isisD13LSPID.name: isisD13LSPID
isisD13LSPID.description: The 8 byte LSP ID, consisting of the SystemID, Circuit ID, and Fragment Number.

isisD13LSPSeq.name: isisD13LSPSeq
isisD13LSPSeq.description: The sequence number for this LSP.

isisD13LSPZeroLife.name: isisD13LSPZeroLife
isisD13LSPZeroLife.description: Is this LSP being purged by this System?

isisD13LSPLifetimeRemain.name: isisD13LSPLifetimeRemain
isisD13LSPLifetimeRemain.description: The remaining lifetime in seconds for this LSP.

isisD13LSPTLVEntry.name: isisD13LSPTLVEntry
isisD13LSPTLVEntry.description: Each entry describes an LSP current stored in the system.

isisD13LSPTLVIndex.name: isisD13LSPTLVIndex
isisD13LSPTLVIndex.description: The index of this TLV in the LSP. The first TLV has index 1 and the Nth TLV has an index of N.

isisD13LSPTLVSeq.name: isisD13LSPTLVSeq
isisD13LSPTLVSeq.description: The sequence number for this LSP.

isisD13NotificationTable.name: isisD13NotificationTable
isisD13NotificationTable.description: Objects seen in the most recent notification this instance of the IS-IS protocol.

isisD13NotificationEntry.name: isisD13NotificationEntry
isisD13NotificationEntry.description: Each entry defines variables relevant to notifications for one instance of the IS-IS protocol.

isisD13PduLspId.name: isisD13PduLspId
isisD13PduLspId.description: An Octet String that uniquely identifies a Link State PDU.

isisD13PduFragment.name: isisD13PduFragment
isisD13PduFragment.description: Holds up to the first 64 bytes of a PDU that triggered the notification.

isisD13PduFieldLen.name: isisD13PduFieldLen
isisD13PduFieldLen.description: Holds the System ID length reported in PDU we received.

isisD13PduMaxAreaAddress.name: isisD13PduMaxAreaAddress
isisD13PduMaxAreaAddress.description: Holds the Max Area Addresses reported in a PDU we received.

isisD13PduProtocolVersion.name: isisD13PduProtocolVersion
isisD13PduProtocolVersion.description: Holds the Protocol version reported in PDU we received.

isisD13PduLspSize.name: isisD13PduLspSize
isisD13PduLspSize.description: Holds the size of LSP we received that is too big to forward.

isisD13PduOriginatingBufferSize.name: isisD13PduOriginatingBufferSize
isisD13PduOriginatingBufferSize.description: Holds the size of isisD13SysOrigLSPBuffSize advertised by peer in TLV.

isisD13PduProtocolsSupported.name: isisD13PduProtocolsSupported
isisD13PduProtocolsSupported.description: The list of protocols supported by an adjacent system. This may be empty.

isisD13AdjState.name: isisD13AdjState
isisD13AdjState.description: The current state of an adjacency.

isisD13PduRemoteRouterID.name: isisD13PduRemoteRouterID
isisD13PduRemoteRouterID.description: The Router ID of a remote system. If not known, we set this to 0.

isisD13DatabaseOverload.name: isisD13DatabaseOverload
isisD13DatabaseOverload.description: This notification is generated when the system enters or leaves the Overload state. The number of times this has be generated and cleared is kept track of by isisD13SysStatLSPDbaseOloads.

isisD13ManualAddressDrops.name: isisD13ManualAddressDrops
isisD13ManualAddressDrops.description: This notification is generated when one of the manual areaAddresses assigned to this system is ignored when computing routes. The object isisD13ManAreaAddrExistState describes the area that has been dropped. The number of times this event has been generated is counted by isisD13SysManAddrDropFromAreas. This notification is edge triggered, and should not be regenerated until an address that was used in the previous computation has been dropped.

isisD13CorruptedLSPDetected.name: isisD13CorruptedLSPDetected
isisD13CorruptedLSPDetected.description: This notification is generated when we find that an LSP that was stored in memory has become corrupted. The number of times this has been generated is counted by isisD13SysCorrLSPs. We forward an LSP ID. We may have independent knowledge of the ID, but in some implementations there is a chance that the ID itself will be corrupted.

isisD13AttemptToExceedMaxSequence.name: isisD13AttemptToExceedMaxSequence
isisD13AttemptToExceedMaxSequence.description: When the sequence number on an LSP we generate wraps the 32 bit sequence counter, we purge and wait to re-announce this information. This notification describes that event. Since these should not be generated rapidly, we generate an event each time this happens. While the first 6 bytes of the LSPID are ours, the other two contain useful information.

isisD13IDLenMismatch.name: isisD13IDLenMismatch
isisD13IDLenMismatch.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with a different value of the System ID Length. This notification includes the an index to identify the circuit where we saw the PDU and the header of the PDU which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from what seem to be the same source. This decision is up to the agent to make, and may be based on the circuit or on some MAC level information.

isisD13MaxAreaAddressesMismatch.name: isisD13MaxAreaAddressesMismatch
isisD13MaxAreaAddressesMismatch.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with a different value of the Maximum Area Addresses. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from what seem to be the same source.

isisD13OwnLSPPurge.name: isisD13OwnLSPPurge
isisD13OwnLSPPurge.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with our systemID and zero age. This notification includes the circuit Index and router ID from the LSP, if available, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion.

isisD13SequenceNumberSkip.name: isisD13SequenceNumberSkip
isisD13SequenceNumberSkip.description: When we receive an LSP with out System ID and different contents, we may need to reissue the LSP with a higher sequence number. We send this notification if we need to increase the sequence number by more than one. If two Intermediate Systems are configured with the same System ID, this notification will fire.

isisD13AuthenticationTypeFailure.name: isisD13AuthenticationTypeFailure
isisD13AuthenticationTypeFailure.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with the wrong authentication type field. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from what seem to be the same source.

isisD13AuthenticationFailure.name: isisD13AuthenticationFailure
isisD13AuthenticationFailure.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with incorrect authentication information field. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from what seem to be the same source.

isisD13VersionSkew.name: isisD13VersionSkew
isisD13VersionSkew.description: A notification sent when we receive a Hello PDU from an IS running a different version of the protocol. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from what seem to be the same source. This decision is up to the agent to make, and may be based on the circuit or on some MAC level information.

isisD13AreaMismatch.name: isisD13AreaMismatch
isisD13AreaMismatch.description: A notification sent when we receive a Hello PDU from an IS which does not share any area address. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from what seem to be the same source. This decision is up to the agent to make, and may be based on the circuit or on some MAC level information.

isisD13RejectedAdjacency.name: isisD13RejectedAdjacency
isisD13RejectedAdjacency.description: A notification sent when we receive a Hello PDU from an IS, but do not establish an adjacency for some reason. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the same source.

isisD13LSPTooLargeToPropagate.name: isisD13LSPTooLargeToPropagate
isisD13LSPTooLargeToPropagate.description: A notification sent when we attempt to propagate an LSP which is larger than the dataLinkBlockSize for the circuit. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the same source.

isisD13OrigLSPBuffSizeMismatch.name: isisD13OrigLSPBuffSizeMismatch
isisD13OrigLSPBuffSizeMismatch.description: A notification sent when a Level 1 LSP or Level 2 LSP is received which is larger than the local value for isisD13OriginatingBufferSize, or when an LSP is received containing the isisD13OriginatingBufferSize option and the value in the PDU option field does not match the local value for isisD13OriginatingBufferSize. We pass up the size from the option field or the size of the LSP that exceeds our configuration. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the same source.

isisD13ProtocolsSupportedMismatch.name: isisD13ProtocolsSupportedMismatch
isisD13ProtocolsSupportedMismatch.description: A notification sent when a non-pseudonode segment 0 LSP is received that has no matching protocols supported. This may be because the system does not generate the field, or because there are no common elements. The list of protocols supported should be included in the notification: it may be empty if the TLV is not supported, or if the TLV is empty. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the same source.

isisD13AdjacencyChange.name: isisD13AdjacencyChange
isisD13AdjacencyChange.description: A notification sent when an adjacency changes state, entering or leaving state up. The first 6 bytes of the isisD13PduLspId are the SystemID of the adjacent IS. The isisD13AdjState is the new state of the adjacency.

isisD13Compliance.name: isisD13Compliance
isisD13Compliance.description: The compliance statement for agents that support the IS-IS MIB

isisD13AdvancedCompliance.name: isisD13AdvancedCompliance
isisD13AdvancedCompliance.description: The compliance statement for agents that support the IS-IS MIB

isisD13SystemGroup.name: isisD13SystemGroup
isisD13SystemGroup.description: The collections of objects used to manage an IS-IS router.

isisD13CircuitGroup.name: isisD13CircuitGroup
isisD13CircuitGroup.description: The collection of objects used to describe in IS-IS Circuit.

isisD13ISAdjGroup.name: isisD13ISAdjGroup
isisD13ISAdjGroup.description: The collections of objects used to manage an IS-IS Adjacency.

isisD13NotificationObjectGroup.name: isisD13NotificationObjectGroup
isisD13NotificationObjectGroup.description: The objects used to record notification parameters.

isisD13NotificationGroup.name: isisD13NotificationGroup
isisD13NotificationGroup.description: The collections of notifications sent by an IS.

isisD13ISPDUCounterGroup.name: isisD13ISPDUCounterGroup
isisD13ISPDUCounterGroup.description: The collections of objects used to count protocol PDUs.

isisD13RATableGroup.name: isisD13RATableGroup
isisD13RATableGroup.description: The collections of objects used to manage the reachable NSAP prefixes.

isisD13ISIPRADestGroup.name: isisD13ISIPRADestGroup
isisD13ISIPRADestGroup.description: The collections of objects used to manage configured IP addresses.

isisD13LSPGroup.name: isisD13LSPGroup
isisD13LSPGroup.description: The collections of objects used to observe the LSP Data Base.
